  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "While developing locally, you can set benchmark baselines, compare against a baseline, or compare two different baselines.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Local-developer-workflow",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "Local developer workflow",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Typical workflow for a developer who wants to track performance metrics on the local machine while during performance work, would be to store one or more baselines (either default or named baselines), with e.g:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package --allow-writing-to-package-directory benchmark baseline update"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "or",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package --allow-writing-to-package-directory benchmark baseline alpha update"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "then while working, simply compare current state of local repo with the previously recorded baseline:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package benchmark baseline compare"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "or",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package benchmark compare alpha"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "If you have stored multiple baselines (for example for different approaches to solving a given performance issue), you can easily compare the two approaches by using named baselines for each and then compare them:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "swift package benchmark compare alpha beta"
          ],
          "syntax" : null,
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Debugging-crashing-benchmarks",
          "level" : 4,
          "text" : "Debugging crashing benchmarks",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The benchmark executables are set up to automatically run all tests when run standalone with simple debug output - this is to enable workflows where the benchmark is run in the Xcode debugger or with Instruments if desired - or with ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "lldb",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " on the command line on Linux to support debugging in problematic performance tests.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "GitHub-CI-workflow",
          "level" : 3,
          "text" : "GitHub CI workflow",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For GitHub, there are sample workflows provided:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Delta comparison workflow, which will run the benchmark on both the pull request and the ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "code" : "main",
                      "type" : "codeVoice"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " branch and compare the results with the specified thresholds and fail\/succeed the workflow accordingly. It also makes a comment into the PR with the results (which will be updated with subsequent runs of the workflow for the PR)",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Simple benchmark - simply runs the benchmark test suite on the pull request and update a separate PR commend with a link to the results.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "For reproducible and good comparable results, it is ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "highly",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "text" : " recommended to set up a private GitHub runner that is",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "dedicated to performance benchmark runs.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
